## CSS-only fix in snippets/css-overrides.liquid

Add (after the existing blog .rte img rule at line 138-143):

```css
/* CLS fix YYYY-MM-DD <bd-id> — Pro Blogger related-articles thumbnails.
   snippets/pro-blogger.snippet.related-item.liquid renders <img> without
   width/height attrs (lines 5 + 20); image URLs use Shopify CDN
   ?height=400 query param so they're 400px tall but variable width.
   Without dimensions, each thumbnail shifts content as it loads —
   6+ thumbnails per blog post = CLS 0.52 on
   hair-education/purple-vs-blue-shampoo-philippines (POOR bucket, GSC
   5/10). Existing article-content-with-img-dims snippet doesn't
   recognize ?height= query params, only _WxH.ext patterns.

   Reserve 1:1 aspect-ratio (matches typical thumbnail container style
   per .pb_image_wrapper) so browser allocates space before image loads.
   width:100% lets the image fill its parent. height:auto + object-fit:
   cover preserves visual fit when actual image aspect differs from 1:1.
   background reserves a visible placeholder color during load. */
.pb_image_wrapper img:not([width]):not([height]) {
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
  background: #f4f6f8;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* Same pattern for .responsive-wide-image which also renders unsized
   in some article contexts (cross-post-blogs widget). 16:9 fallback
   matches the existing .blog__article__content rule at line 138-143. */
.responsive-wide-image:not([width]):not([height]) {
  aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9;
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
  background: #f4f6f8;
}
```

Files: snippets/css-overrides.liquid (CSS-only, ~30 lines).

Match existing CLS-fix comment convention: `/* CLS fix YYYY-MM-DD <bd-id> — <reason> */`.

Optional follow-up (not in this scope): edit pro-blogger.snippet.related-item.liquid lines 5 + 20 to add explicit `width="400" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async"` attributes to the <img> tags. CSS-only fix is sufficient for CLS but Liquid edit also helps the browser preconnect/prioritize correctly. Filed as a P3 follow-up if/when this surfaces in GSC again.

## Implementation: document.createElement guard

Place the following inline `<script>` block in layout/theme.liquid IMMEDIATELY before line 683 ({{ content_for_header }}):

```liquid
{%- comment -%}
  VQB performance gate (bd hairmnl-theme-XXXX):
  VisualQuizBuilder loads 447KB on every page via SATCB dynamic injection.
  Only needed on /apps/quiz routes. Block on everything else.
  Guard runs before content_for_header so document.createElement is
  overridden before SATCB fires (SATCB executes post-DOM-parse via async scripts).
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
(function() {
  var VQB_ORIGINS = ['cdn.visualquizbuilder.com'];
  var QUIZ_PATHS = ['/apps/quiz'];
  var path = window.location.pathname;
  var allowed = QUIZ_PATHS.some(function(p) { return path === p || path.indexOf(p + '/') === 0; });
  if (allowed) return; // quiz page — let VQB load normally

  var _createElement = document.createElement.bind(document);
  document.createElement = function(tag) {
    var el = _createElement.apply(document, arguments);
    if (typeof tag === 'string' && tag.toLowerCase() === 'script') {
      var _setSrc = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(HTMLScriptElement.prototype, 'src').set;
      var blocked = false;
      Object.defineProperty(el, 'src', {
        configurable: true,
        get: function() {
          return Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(HTMLScriptElement.prototype, 'src').get.call(this);
        },
        set: function(v) {
          if (!blocked && VQB_ORIGINS.some(function(o) { return String(v).indexOf(o) !== -1; })) {
            blocked = true;
            return; // swallow the src assignment — script never fetches
          }
          _setSrc.call(this, v);
        }
      });
    }
    return el;
  };

  // MutationObserver fallback: catch any <script src="...vqb..."> added via innerHTML
  var observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
    mutations.forEach(function(m) {
      m.addedNodes.forEach(function(node) {
        if (node.tagName === 'SCRIPT' && node.src &&
            VQB_ORIGINS.some(function(o) { return node.src.indexOf(o) !== -1; })) {
          node.parentNode && node.parentNode.removeChild(node);
        }
      });
    });
  });
  observer.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>
```

## Placement in theme.liquid

Insert block BEFORE line 683. Final order:
```
  ... (loyaltylion snippet at line 680) ...

  <!-- VQB performance gate -->
  <script>... guard ...</script>

  <!-- Shopify app scripts -->
  {{ content_for_header }}
```

## Risk audit

1. **SATCB uses fetch()+eval() instead of createElement** — Unlikely (SATCB injects standard <script> tags per industry convention), but if so, guard won't intercept. Mitigation: After deploy, run PSI and check network_by_origin. If VQB still appears, add a fetch() interceptor.

2. **VQB widget embedded inline on non-quiz page via section** — Would still render a div placeholder, but without the JS it won't hydrate. Acceptable degradation.

3. **VQB initializes via a window listener (not createElement)** — If VQB uses `window.addEventListener('load', ...)` with the script already inline from content_for_header — but confirmed it's NOT in content_for_header. Non-issue.

4. **MutationObserver disconnection** — Observer runs for full session. No disconnect call needed since the guard should only be active when !allowed. Negligible memory cost.

5. **False-negative on quiz page** — QUIZ_PATHS check is path.startsWith('/apps/quiz'). Shopify quiz page at /apps/quiz or /apps/quiz/[slug] — both covered. If quiz is on a custom /pages/quiz URL, add to QUIZ_PATHS.

6. **createElement override survives to SATCB timing** — SATCB scripts are async, parsed and executed AFTER DOM parsing. The guard is a synchronous inline script before content_for_header, so it will always run first.

7. **Third-party scripts sharing mustache.js** — VQB likely brings mustache.js as a dep; blocking VQB's creator script means mustache.js may not load either. Mustache.js appears nowhere else in the theme. Non-issue.

## Verification steps

1. Draft theme push (`--theme=140785582179 --only=layout/theme.liquid`)
2. Browse https://www.hairmnl.com/ in incognito → DevTools Network → confirm NO requests to cdn.visualquizbuilder.com
3. Browse https://www.hairmnl.com/apps/quiz → confirm quiz loads and functions
4. Run PSI mobile on homepage → confirm cdn.visualquizbuilder.com absent from network_by_origin
5. If clean: push to live theme 131664707683 with --allow-live
6. Run dashboard refresh to capture new PSI baseline (should show ~447KB reduction in mobile payload)

## Out of scope
- BookThatApp gating (xex) — same pattern, file separately
- Removing VQB's dns-prefetch hint in theme.liquid line 85 (minor, clean up in same PR)
- Investigating SATCB to understand full script manifest

